                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <sic>Pittsburg</sic>
                                        </placeName>
                                        <date>September 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">I was <sic>somwatte</sic> astonished to<lb/> see
                                        in News <sic>itemes</sic>, in your last Occident the
                                        Election of a =<lb/>
                                        <persName>Rev. Mr Rubinson</persName> in
                                                  <placeName><sic>Richmont</sic> Va.</placeName>
                                        <sic>wich</sic> you announced<lb/> with such pleasure to
                                        your readers,</p>
                              <p>Now sir let me tell you that about five or six <sic>wheeks</sic> ago<lb/>
                                        <sic>ther</sic> was here a man who called himself
                                                  <persName>Mr Rubinson</persName><lb/> Dr of Phi,
                                        at that time <persName>Mr Rubinson</persName> in presence of<lb/>
                                        <persName>Rev Mr Mareuson</persName> Hasan of our
                                        congregation and<lb/> Gentlemen from
                                                  <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> by the name of
                                                  <persName>Mr Cohen</persName><lb/> Now in
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> (at
                                                  <persName>Mr Goldschmits </persName>Tavern)<lb/>
                                        both Israelites he denied <sic>possitivly</sic> that he was
                                        no<lb/> Israelite, and as he expressed himself his
                                        father<lb/> a born <add>Hebrew</add> and has nothing to do
                                        with the Jewish<lb/> Religion, and as far as I know
                                                  <sic>dit</sic> not Lodge by<lb/> any
                                                  <add>Hebrew</add> here, but he <sic>dit</sic> know
                                        that <sic>ther</sic> was a<lb/> Jewish <sic>benefial</sic>
                                        society <sic>her</sic>
                                        <sic>wher</sic> he <sic>applid</sic> for benefit<lb/> but
                                        the <sic>Presitent</sic> of the society being apprised that
                                        he<lb/> has <sic>deniet</sic> of being a Jew told him the
                                                  <sic>socity</sic> was only<lb/> and alone for poor
                                                  <sic>Jewes</sic>, to <sic>wich</sic> he said
                                        what<lb/> difference it could be to him what he was.</p>
                              <p>Now sir let me ask you if such a <sic>intivitual</sic><lb/> as the
                                        one who was here in
                                                  <placeName><sic>Pittsburg</sic></placeName> should
                                        be taken<lb/> up by any congregation what benefit will a
                                        congre=<lb/>gation receive from such a character, that
                                        is=</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>the way I look at it, (as I myself <sic>hav</sic> been
                                        traveling<lb/> for about seven years among
                                                  <sic>Gentils</sic> but never <sic>deniet</sic>
                                        my<lb/> Religion) I am only a <sic>comen</sic> man and
                                                  <sic>hav</sic>
                                        <sic>verry</sic>
                                        <sic>littel</sic><lb/> or no learning, but still it strikes
                                        me and makes me<lb/> feel <sic>verry</sic> anxious to see
                                        such a thing, should be true<lb/> would not a congregation
                                        be better without Hasan<lb/> than to have such a one</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Now <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> as I know<lb/>
                                        that you are a <sic>gread</sic> man for promoting
                                                  <sic>Jewdism</sic><lb/> among the <sic>Jewes</sic>
                                        and that you try your best to make<lb/> the
                                                  <add>Hebrew</add> what they ought to be please and
                                        give <del>give</del><lb/> yourself a <sic>littel</sic>
                                        <sic>troble</sic> you will find <persName>Mr
                                                  Cohen</persName> from<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> in
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> and inquire of
                                        him <sic>abut</sic><lb/> what I wrote above, that is if you
                                        think that I may be<lb/> only a <sic>littel</sic> right, I
                                        may be wrong, that is that a men<lb/> may do all those
                                        things and more too, and still may<lb/> be taken up as Hasan
                                        and Lecturer in a Jewish cong<lb/>regation.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir I tell you <sic>cantitly</sic> that I am
                                        ignorant<lb/> in Religion matters, I think I only know our
                                        common<lb/> every day practices, all I wrote you that
                                        for<lb/> is that I could not help to think <sic>joust</sic>
                                        as I<lb/> wrote you, your will be kind <sic>enouff</sic> and
                                        forgive<lb/> my <sic>ignorence</sic></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">With that I remain yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <persName role="author">N. Gellinger</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
